---
import { CommunityWorkflow } from "@/components/react/sections/CommunityWorkflow";
import { CornerPlus } from "@/components/react/ui/corner-plus";
---

<section id="parallel" class="border-t border-border">
	<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-6">
		<div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-2 p-6 sm:p-8 md:p-10 lg:p-14 md:sticky md:top-20 md:self-start flex flex-col gap-6">
			<p class="reveal font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider text-accent">
				What it'll feel like
			</p>
			<h3
				class="reveal text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tighter text-balance"
				style="--reveal-delay: 100ms"
			>
				A weekend sprint. Three tracks. One ship.
			</h3>
			<p
				class="reveal text-base text-text-secondary leading-relaxed"
				style="--reveal-delay: 200ms"
			>
				When we open the platform, you'll be paired with a frontend, a backend,
				and a designer for a focused weekend sprint. Real-time progress on each
				track. The point is to ship something together, not collect badges alone.
			</p>
			<p
				class="reveal font-mono text-xs text-text-muted"
				style="--reveal-delay: 300ms"
			>
				This is a preview · sprints start after launch
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-4 w-full border-t md:border-t-0 md:border-l border-border relative">
			<CornerPlus position="all" className="text-text-muted/40" />
			<CommunityWorkflow client:visible />
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
